  223. /* Switch from OCaml to C stack. Clobbers %r10, %r11. */
  224. #ifdef ASM_CFI_SUPPORTED
  225. ‌#define SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C_CFI                                   \
  226.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE;                                     \
  227.           /* %rsp points to the c_stack_link. */                \
  228.         .cfi_escape DW_CFA_def_cfa_expression, 5,               \
  229.            DW_OP_breg + DW_REG_rsp, Cstack_sp, DW_OP_deref,     \
  230.            DW_OP_plus_uconst, RETADDR_ENTRY_SIZE
  231. #else
  232. ‌#define SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C_CFI
  233. #endif
  234. ‌#define SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C                                  \
  235.     /* Fill in Caml_state->current_stack->sp */            \
  236.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %r10;           \
  237.         movq    %rsp, Stack_sp(%r10);                      \
  238.     /* Fill in Caml_state->c_stack */                      \
  239.         movq    Caml_state(c_stack), %r11;                 \
  240.         movq    %rsp, Cstack_sp(%r11);                     \
  241.         movq    %r10, Cstack_stack(%r11);                  \
  242.     /* Switch to C stack */                                \
  243.         movq    %r11, %rsp;                                \
  244.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C_CFI

  246. /* Switch from C to OCaml stack.  Clobbers %r11. */
  247. ‌#define SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML                                           \
  248.     /* Assert that %rsp == Caml_state->c_stack &&
  249.         Caml_state->c_stack->sp == Caml_state->current_stack->sp */ \
  250.         IF_DEBUG(cmpq %rsp, Caml_state(c_stack); je 8f; int3; 8:    \
  251.                  movq Caml_state(current_stack), %r11;              \
  252.                  movq Stack_sp(%r11), %r11;                         \
  253.                  cmpq %r11, Cstack_sp(%rsp); je 8f; int3; 8:)       \
  254.         movq    Cstack_sp(%rsp), %rsp;                              \
  255.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE

  257. /* Load Caml_state->exn_handler into %rsp and restores prior exn_handler.
  258.    Clobbers %r10 and %r11. */
  259. ‌#define RESTORE_EXN_HANDLER_OCAML              \

  264. /* Switch between OCaml stacks. Clobbers %r12.
  265.    Expects old stack in %rsi and target stack in %r10.
  266.    Leaves old stack in %rsi and target stack in %r10. */
  267. ‌#define SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS                               \
  268.         ENTER_FUNCTION                                    \
  269.     /* Save OCaml SP and exn_handler in the stack info */ \
  270.         movq    %rsp, Stack_sp(%rsi);                     \
  271.         movq    Caml_state(exn_handler), %r12;            \
  272.         movq    %r12, Stack_exception(%rsi);              \
  273.     /* switch stacks */                                   \
  274.         movq    %r10, Caml_state(current_stack);          \
  275.         movq    Stack_sp(%r10), %rsp;                     \
  276.         CFI_DEF_CFA_OFFSET(8);                            \
  277.     /* restore exn_handler for new stack */               \
  278.         movq    Stack_exception(%r10), %r12;              \
  279.         movq    %r12, Caml_state(exn_handler);            \
  280.         LEAVE_FUNCTION

  282. /* Updates the oldest saved frame pointer in the target fiber.

  284.    A fiber stack may need to grow, causing the reallocation of the entire fiber,
  285.    including stack_info and stack_handler structures.
  286.    caml_try_realloc_stack will not be able to update the linked list of
  287.    frame-pointers if it has been split (ie, in a continuation).
  288.    caml_resume and caml_reperform use this macro to update the oldest saved rbp
  289.    (highest one in the stack) in case the fiber was reallocated to reattach the
  290.    frame-pointer linked list.

  292.    REG: Stack_handler(target_fiber)

  294.    The frame pointer will be pushed into the stack immediately after these
  295.    instructions. The offset of the oldest saved rbp in a fiber from the stack
  296.    handler is 48 = 4 words (caml_runstack) + 2 words (rip and rbp).
  297.    */
  298. #ifdef WITH_FRAME_POINTERS
  299. ‌#define UPDATE_BASE_POINTER(REG)                          \
  300.         leaq    -8(%rsp), %r11;                           \
  301.         movq    %r11, -48(REG)
  302. #else
  303. ‌#define UPDATE_BASE_POINTER(REG)
  304. #endif

  354.         popq    %rsi; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(rsi);  \
  355.         popq    %rbp; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(rbp);  \
  356.         popq    %rbx; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(rbx)

  358. #else

  360. /* Unix API: callee-save regs are rbx, rbp, r12-r15 */

  362. ‌#define PUSH_CALLEE_SAVE_REGS \
  363.         pushq   %rbx; CFI_ADJUST(8); CFI_OFFSET(rbx, -16); \
  364.         pushq   %rbp; CFI_ADJUST(8); CFI_OFFSET(rbp, -24); \
  365.         pushq   %r12; CFI_ADJUST(8); CFI_OFFSET(r12, -32); \
  366.         pushq   %r13; CFI_ADJUST(8); CFI_OFFSET(r13, -40); \
  367.         pushq   %r14; CFI_ADJUST(8); CFI_OFFSET(r14, -48); \
  368.         pushq   %r15; CFI_ADJUST(8); CFI_OFFSET(r15, -56)

  370. ‌#define POP_CALLEE_SAVE_REGS \
  371.         popq    %r15; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(r15); \
  372.         popq    %r14; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(r14); \
  373.         popq    %r13; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(r13); \
  374.         popq    %r12; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(r12); \
  375.         popq    %rbp; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(rbp); \
  376.         popq    %rbx; CFI_ADJUST(-8); CFI_SAME_VALUE(rbx)

  378. #endif

  380. ‌#define C_call(target) CHECK_STACK_ALIGNMENT; call target

  382. /******************************************************************************/
  383. /* Registers holding arguments of C functions. */
  384. /******************************************************************************/

  386. #if defined(SYS_mingw64) || defined(SYS_cygwin)
  387. ‌#define C_ARG_1 %rcx
  388. ‌#define C_ARG_2 %rdx
  389. ‌#define C_ARG_3 %r8
  390. ‌#define C_ARG_4 %r9
  391. #else
  392. ‌#define C_ARG_1 %rdi
  393. ‌#define C_ARG_2 %rsi
  394. ‌#define C_ARG_3 %rdx
  395. ‌#define C_ARG_4 %rcx
  396. #endif

  398.         .text

  400. #if defined(FUNCTION_SECTIONS)
  401.         TEXT_SECTION(caml_hot.code_begin)
  402.         .globl  G(caml_hot.code_begin)
  403. G(caml_hot.code_begin):

  405.         TEXT_SECTION(caml_hot.code_end)
  406.         .globl  G(caml_hot.code_end)
  407. G(caml_hot.code_end):
  408. #endif

  412. /******************************************************************************/

  415.         .globl  G(caml_system__code_begin)

  418.         caml_system__code_begin instead of caml_call_gc */

  420. /******************************************************************************/
  421. /* Allocation */
  422. /******************************************************************************/

  424. /* Save all of the registers that may be in use to a free gc_regs bucket.
  425.    Returns: bucket in %r15. Clobbers %r11 (after saving it) */
  426. ‌#define SAVE_ALL_REGS                                  \
  427.     /* First, save the young_ptr. */                   \
  428.         movq    %r15, Caml_state(young_ptr);           \
  429.     /* Now, use %r15 to point to the gc_regs bucket */ \
  430.     /* We save %r11 first to allow it to be scratch */ \
  431.         movq    Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets), %r15;     \
  432.         movq    %r11, 11*8(%r15);                      \
  433.         movq    0(%r15), %r11; /* next ptr */          \
  434.         movq    %r11, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets);     \
  435.         movq    %rax,         0*8(%r15);               \
  436.         movq    %rbx,         1*8(%r15);               \
  437.         movq    %rdi,         2*8(%r15);               \
  438.         movq    %rsi,         3*8(%r15);               \
  439.         movq    %rdx,         4*8(%r15);               \
  440.         movq    %rcx,         5*8(%r15);               \
  441.         movq    %r8,          6*8(%r15);               \
  442.         movq    %r9,          7*8(%r15);               \
  443.         movq    %r12,         8*8(%r15);               \
  444.         movq    %r13,         9*8(%r15);               \
  445.         movq    %r10,        10*8(%r15);               \
  446.              /* %r11 is at   11*8(%r15); */            \
  447.         movq    %rbp,        12*8(%r15);               \
  448.         movsd   %xmm0,   (0+13)*8(%r15);               \
  449.         movsd   %xmm1,   (1+13)*8(%r15);               \
  450.         movsd   %xmm2,   (2+13)*8(%r15);               \
  451.         movsd   %xmm3,   (3+13)*8(%r15);               \
  452.         movsd   %xmm4,   (4+13)*8(%r15);               \
  453.         movsd   %xmm5,   (5+13)*8(%r15);               \
  454.         movsd   %xmm6,   (6+13)*8(%r15);               \
  455.         movsd   %xmm7,   (7+13)*8(%r15);               \
  456.         movsd   %xmm8,   (8+13)*8(%r15);               \
  457.         movsd   %xmm9,   (9+13)*8(%r15);               \
  458.         movsd   %xmm10, (10+13)*8(%r15);               \
  459.         movsd   %xmm11, (11+13)*8(%r15);               \
  460.         movsd   %xmm12, (12+13)*8(%r15);               \
  461.         movsd   %xmm13, (13+13)*8(%r15);               \
  462.         movsd   %xmm14, (14+13)*8(%r15);               \
  463.         movsd   %xmm15, (15+13)*8(%r15)

  465. /* Undo SAVE_ALL_REGS. Expects gc_regs bucket in %r15 */
  466. ‌#define RESTORE_ALL_REGS                               \
  467.     /* Restore %rax, freeing up the next ptr slot */   \
  468.         movq    0*8(%r15), %rax;                       \
  469.         movq    Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets), %r11;     \
  470.         movq    %r11, 0(%r15); /* next ptr */          \
  471.         movq    %r15, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets);     \
  472.            /* above:  0*8(%r15),%rax; */               \
  473.         movq          1*8(%r15),%rbx;                  \
  474.         movq          2*8(%r15),%rdi;                  \
  475.         movq          3*8(%r15),%rsi;                  \
  476.         movq          4*8(%r15),%rdx;                  \
  477.         movq          5*8(%r15),%rcx;                  \
  478.         movq          6*8(%r15),%r8;                   \
  479.         movq          7*8(%r15),%r9;                   \
  480.         movq          8*8(%r15),%r12;                  \
  481.         movq          9*8(%r15),%r13;                  \
  482.         movq         10*8(%r15),%r10;                  \
  483.         movq         11*8(%r15),%r11;                  \
  484.         movq         12*8(%r15),%rbp;                  \
  485.         movsd    (0+13)*8(%r15),%xmm0;                 \
  486.         movsd    (1+13)*8(%r15),%xmm1;                 \
  487.         movsd    (2+13)*8(%r15),%xmm2;                 \
  488.         movsd    (3+13)*8(%r15),%xmm3;                 \
  489.         movsd    (4+13)*8(%r15),%xmm4;                 \
  490.         movsd    (5+13)*8(%r15),%xmm5;                 \
  491.         movsd    (6+13)*8(%r15),%xmm6;                 \
  492.         movsd    (7+13)*8(%r15),%xmm7;                 \
  493.         movsd    (8+13)*8(%r15),%xmm8;                 \
  494.         movsd    (9+13)*8(%r15),%xmm9;                 \
  495.         movsd   (10+13)*8(%r15),%xmm10;                \
  496.         movsd   (11+13)*8(%r15),%xmm11;                \
  497.         movsd   (12+13)*8(%r15),%xmm12;                \
  498.         movsd   (13+13)*8(%r15),%xmm13;                \
  499.         movsd   (14+13)*8(%r15),%xmm14;                \
  500.         movsd   (15+13)*8(%r15),%xmm15;                \
  501.         movq    Caml_state(young_ptr), %r15

  503. FUNCTION(G(caml_call_realloc_stack))
  504. CFI_STARTPROC
  505.         CFI_SIGNAL_FRAME
  506.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  507.         SAVE_ALL_REGS
  508.         movq    RETADDR_ENTRY_SIZE(%rsp), C_ARG_1 /* argument */
  509.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  510.         C_call  (GCALL(caml_try_realloc_stack))
  511.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  512.         cmpq    $0, %rax
  513.         jz      1f
  514.         RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  515.         LEAVE_FUNCTION
  516.         ret
  517. 1:      RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  518.         LEA_VAR(caml_exn_Stack_overflow, %rax)
  519.         add     $16, %rsp /* pop argument, retaddr */
  520.         jmp     GCALL(caml_raise_exn)
  521. CFI_ENDPROC
  522. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_call_realloc_stack))

  524. FUNCTION(G(caml_call_gc))
  525. CFI_STARTPROC
  526.         CFI_SIGNAL_FRAME
  527.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  528. LBL(caml_call_gc):
  529.         SAVE_ALL_REGS
  530.         movq    %r15, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  531.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  532.         C_call (GCALL(caml_garbage_collection))
  533.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  534.         movq    Caml_state(gc_regs), %r15
  535.         RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  536.         LEAVE_FUNCTION
  537.         ret
  538. CFI_ENDPROC
  539. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_call_gc))

  541. FUNCTION(G(caml_alloc1))
  542. CFI_STARTPROC
  543.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  544.         subq    $16, %r15
  545.         cmpq    Caml_state(young_limit), %r15
  546.         jb      LBL(caml_call_gc)
  547.         LEAVE_FUNCTION
  548.         ret
  549. CFI_ENDPROC
  550. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_alloc1))

  552. FUNCTION(G(caml_alloc2))

  556.         cmpq    Caml_state(young_limit), %r15
  557.         jb      LBL(caml_call_gc)
  558.         LEAVE_FUNCTION

  560. CFI_ENDPROC
  561. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_alloc2))

  584. /******************************************************************************/
  585. /* Call a C function from OCaml */
  586. /******************************************************************************/

  588. FUNCTION(G(caml_c_call))
  589. CFI_STARTPROC
  590.         CFI_SIGNAL_FRAME
  591.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  592. LBL(caml_c_call):
  593.     /* Arguments:
  594.         C arguments         : %rdi, %rsi, %rdx, %rcx, %r8, and %r9
  595.         C function          : %rax */
  596.     /* Switch from OCaml to C */
  597.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  598.     /* Make the alloc ptr available to the C code */
  599.         movq    %r15, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  600.     /* Call the function (address in %rax) */
  601.         C_call  (*%rax)
  602.     /* Prepare for return to OCaml */
  603.         movq    Caml_state(young_ptr), %r15
  604.     /* Load ocaml stack and restore global variables */
  605.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  606.         LEAVE_FUNCTION
  607.     /* Return to OCaml caller */
  608.         ret
  609. CFI_ENDPROC
  610. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_c_call))

  612. FUNCTION(G(caml_c_call_stack_args))
  613. CFI_STARTPROC
  614.         CFI_SIGNAL_FRAME
  615.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  616.     /* Arguments:
  617.         C arguments         : %rdi, %rsi, %rdx, %rcx, %r8, and %r9
  618.         C function          : %rax
  619.         C stack args        : begin=%r13 end=%r12 */
  620.     /* Switch from OCaml to C */
  621.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  622.     /* we use %rbx (otherwise unused) to enable backtraces */
  623.         movq    %rsp, %rbx
  624. #ifdef ASM_CFI_SUPPORTED
  625.         .cfi_escape DW_CFA_def_cfa_expression, 5,           \
  626.           /* %rbp points to the c_stack_link structure */   \
  627.           DW_OP_breg + DW_REG_rbx, Cstack_sp, DW_OP_deref,  \
  628.           DW_OP_plus_uconst, RETADDR_ENTRY_SIZE
  629. #endif
  630.     /* Make the alloc ptr available to the C code */
  631.         movq    %r15, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  632.     /* Copy arguments from OCaml to C stack */
  633. #if defined(SYS_mingw64) || defined (SYS_cygwin)
  634.         addq    $32, %rsp
  635. #endif
  636. LBL(105):
  637.         subq    $8, %r12
  638.         cmpq    %r13,%r12
  639.         jb      LBL(106)
  640.         push    (%r12); CFI_ADJUST(8)
  641.         jmp     LBL(105)
  642. LBL(106):
  643. #if defined(SYS_mingw64) || defined (SYS_cygwin)
  644.         subq    $32, %rsp
  645. #endif
  646.     /* Call the function (address in %rax) */
  647.         C_call  (*%rax)
  648.     /* Pop arguments back off the stack */
  649.         movq    Caml_state(c_stack), %rsp
  650.     /* Prepare for return to OCaml */
  651.         movq    Caml_state(young_ptr), %r15
  652.     /* Load ocaml stack and restore global variables */
  653.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  654.     /* Return to OCaml caller */
  655.         LEAVE_FUNCTION
  656.         ret
  657. CFI_ENDPROC
  658. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_c_call_stack_args))

  660. /******************************************************************************/
  661. /* Start the OCaml program */
  662. /******************************************************************************/

  664. FUNCTION(G(caml_start_program))
  665. CFI_STARTPROC
  666.         CFI_SIGNAL_FRAME
  667.     /* Save callee-save registers */
  668.         PUSH_CALLEE_SAVE_REGS
  669.     /* Load Caml_state into r14 (was passed as an argument from C) */
  670.         movq    C_ARG_1, %r14
  671.     /* Initial entry point is G(caml_program) */
  672.         LEA_VAR(caml_program, %r12)
  673. #ifdef DEBUG
  674.         movq    $0, %rax  /* dummy */
  675.         movq    $0, %rbx  /* dummy */
  676.         movq    $0, %rdi  /* dummy */
  677.         movq    $0, %rsi  /* dummy */
  678. #endif
  679.     /* Common code for caml_start_program and caml_callback* */
  680. LBL(caml_start_program):
  681.     /* Load young_ptr into %r15 */
  682.         movq    Caml_state(young_ptr), %r15
  683.     /* Build struct c_stack_link on the C stack */
  684.         subq    $SIZEOF_C_STACK_LINK, %rsp; CFI_ADJUST(SIZEOF_C_STACK_LINK)
  685.         movq    $0, Cstack_stack(%rsp)
  686.         movq    $0, Cstack_sp(%rsp)
  687.         movq    Caml_state(c_stack), %r10
  688.         movq    %r10, Cstack_prev(%rsp)
  689.         movq    %rsp, Caml_state(c_stack)
  690.         CHECK_STACK_ALIGNMENT
  691.     /* Load the OCaml stack. */
  692.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %r11
  693.         movq    Stack_sp(%r11), %r10
  694.     /* Store the stack pointer to allow DWARF unwind */
  695.         subq    $16, %r10
  696.         movq    %rsp, 0(%r10) /* C_STACK_SP */
  697.     /* Store the gc_regs for callbacks during a GC */
  698.         movq    Caml_state(gc_regs), %r11
  699.         movq    %r11, 8(%r10)
  700.     /* Build a handler for exceptions raised in OCaml on the OCaml stack. */
  701.         subq    $16, %r10
  702.         lea     LBL(109)(%rip), %r11
  703.         movq    %r11, 8(%r10)
  704.     /* link in the previous exn_handler so that copying stacks works */
  705.         movq    Caml_state(exn_handler), %r11
  706.         movq    %r11, 0(%r10)
  707.         movq    %r10, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  708.     /* Switch stacks and call the OCaml code */
  709.         movq    %r10, %rsp
  710. #ifdef ASM_CFI_SUPPORTED
  711.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  712.         .cfi_escape DW_CFA_def_cfa_expression, 3 + 2,                 \
  713.             /* %rsp points to the exn handler on the OCaml stack */   \
  714.             /* %rsp + 16 contains the C_STACK_SP */                   \
  715.           DW_OP_breg + DW_REG_rsp, 16 /* exn handler */, DW_OP_deref, \
  716.           DW_OP_plus_uconst,                                          \
  717.              24  /* struct c_stack_link */ +                          \
  718.              6*8 /* callee save regs */ +                             \
  719.              8   /* ret addr */
  720. #endif
  721.         call    *%r12
  722. LBL(108):
  723.     /* pop exn handler */
  724.         movq    0(%rsp), %r11
  725.         movq    %r11, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  726.         leaq    16(%rsp), %r10
  727. 1:  /* restore GC regs */
  728.         movq    8(%r10), %r11
  729.         movq    %r11, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  730.         addq    $16, %r10
  731.     /* Update alloc ptr */
  732.         movq    %r15, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  733.     /* Return to C stack. */
  734.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %r11
  735.         movq    %r10, Stack_sp(%r11)
  736.         movq    Caml_state(c_stack), %rsp
  737.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  738.     /* Pop the struct c_stack_link */
  739.         movq    Cstack_prev(%rsp), %r10
  740.         movq    %r10, Caml_state(c_stack)
  741.         addq    $SIZEOF_C_STACK_LINK, %rsp; CFI_ADJUST(-SIZEOF_C_STACK_LINK)
  742.     /* Restore callee-save registers. */
  743.         POP_CALLEE_SAVE_REGS
  744.     /* Return to caller. */
  745.         ret
  746. LBL(109):
  747.     /* Exception handler*/
  748.     /* Mark the bucket as an exception result and return it */
  749.         orq     $2, %rax
  750.         /* exn handler already popped here */
  751.         movq    %rsp, %r10
  752.         jmp     1b
  753. CFI_ENDPROC
  754. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_start_program))

  756. /******************************************************************************/
  757. /* Exceptions */
  758. /******************************************************************************/

  760. /* Raise an exception from OCaml */

  762. FUNCTION(G(caml_raise_exn))
  763. CFI_STARTPROC
  764.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  765. LBL(caml_raise_exn):
  766.         testq   $1, Caml_state(backtrace_active)
  767.         jne   LBL(116)
  768.         RESTORE_EXN_HANDLER_OCAML
  769.         ret
  770. LBL(116):
  771.         movq    $0, Caml_state(backtrace_pos)
  772. LBL(117):
  773.         movq    %rsp, %r10        /* Save OCaml stack pointer */
  774.         movq    %rax, %r12        /* Save exception bucket */
  775.         movq    Caml_state(c_stack), %rsp
  776.         movq    %rax, C_ARG_1     /* arg 1: exception bucket */
  777. #ifdef WITH_FRAME_POINTERS
  778.         movq    8(%r10), C_ARG_2   /* arg 2: pc of raise */
  779.         leaq    16(%r10), C_ARG_3  /* arg 3: sp at raise */
  780. #else
  781.         movq    (%r10), C_ARG_2   /* arg 2: pc of raise */
  782.         leaq    8(%r10), C_ARG_3  /* arg 3: sp at raise */
  783. #endif
  784.         movq    Caml_state(exn_handler), C_ARG_4
  785.                                   /* arg 4: sp of handler */
  786.         C_call  (GCALL(caml_stash_backtrace))
  787.         movq    %r12, %rax        /* Recover exception bucket */
  788.         RESTORE_EXN_HANDLER_OCAML
  789.         ret
  790. CFI_ENDPROC
  791. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_raise_exn))

  793. FUNCTION(G(caml_reraise_exn))
  794. CFI_STARTPROC
  795.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  796.         testq   $1, Caml_state(backtrace_active)
  797.         jne   LBL(117)
  798.         RESTORE_EXN_HANDLER_OCAML
  799.         ret
  800. CFI_ENDPROC
  801. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_reraise_exn))

  803. /* Raise an exception from C */

  805. FUNCTION(G(caml_raise_exception))
  806. CFI_STARTPROC
  807.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  808.         movq    C_ARG_1, %r14                /* Caml_state */
  809.         movq    C_ARG_2, %rax
  810.     /* Load young_ptr into %r15 */
  811.         movq    Caml_state(young_ptr), %r15
  812.     /* Discard the C stack pointer and reset to ocaml stack */
  813.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %r10
  814.         movq    Stack_sp(%r10), %rsp         /* FIXME: CFI */
  815.         jmp LBL(caml_raise_exn)
  816. CFI_ENDPROC
  817. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_raise_exception))

  819. /******************************************************************************/
  820. /* Callback from C to OCaml */
  821. /******************************************************************************/

  823. FUNCTION(G(caml_callback_asm))
  824. CFI_STARTPROC
  825.     /* Save callee-save registers */
  826.         PUSH_CALLEE_SAVE_REGS
  827.     /* Initial loading of arguments */
  828.         movq    C_ARG_1, %r14      /* Caml_state */
  829.         movq    C_ARG_2, %rbx      /* closure */
  830.         movq    0(C_ARG_3), %rax   /* argument */
  831.         movq    0(%rbx), %r12      /* code pointer */
  832.         movq    $0, %rdi           /* dummy */
  833.         movq    $0, %rsi           /* dummy */
  834.         jmp     LBL(caml_start_program)
  835. CFI_ENDPROC
  836. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_callback_asm))

  838. FUNCTION(G(caml_callback2_asm))
  839. CFI_STARTPROC
  840.     /* Save callee-save registers */
  841.         PUSH_CALLEE_SAVE_REGS
  842.     /* Initial loading of arguments */
  843.         movq    C_ARG_1, %r14      /* Caml_state */
  844.         movq    C_ARG_2, %rdi      /* closure */
  845.         movq    0(C_ARG_3), %rax   /* first argument */
  846.         movq    8(C_ARG_3), %rbx   /* second argument */
  847.         LEA_VAR(caml_apply2, %r12) /* code pointer */
  848.         movq    $0, %rsi           /* dummy */
  849.         jmp     LBL(caml_start_program)
  850. CFI_ENDPROC
  851. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_callback2_asm))

  853. FUNCTION(G(caml_callback3_asm))
  854. CFI_STARTPROC
  855.     /* Save callee-save registers */
  856.         PUSH_CALLEE_SAVE_REGS
  857.     /* Initial loading of arguments */
  858.         movq    C_ARG_1, %r14      /* Caml_state */
  859.         movq    0(C_ARG_3), %rax   /* first argument */
  860.         movq    8(C_ARG_3), %rbx   /* second argument */
  861.         movq    C_ARG_2, %rsi      /* closure */
  862.         movq    16(C_ARG_3), %rdi  /* third argument */
  863.         LEA_VAR(caml_apply3, %r12) /* code pointer */
  864.         jmp     LBL(caml_start_program)
  865. CFI_ENDPROC
  866. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_callback3_asm))

  868. /******************************************************************************/
  869. /* Fibers */
  870. /*
  871. * A continuation is a one word object that points to a fiber. A fiber [f] will
  872. * point to its parent at Handler_parent(Stack_handler(f)). In the following,
  873. * the [last_fiber] refers to the last fiber in the linked-list formed by the
  874. * parent pointer.
  875. */
  876. /******************************************************************************/

  878. FUNCTION(G(caml_perform))
  879. CFI_STARTPROC
  880.     /*  %rax: effect to perform
  881.         %rbx: freshly allocated continuation */
  882.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %rsi /* %rsi := old stack */
  883.         leaq    1(%rsi), %rdi /* %rdi (last_fiber) := Val_ptr(old stack) */
  884.         movq    %rdi, 0(%rbx) /* Initialise continuation */
  885. LBL(do_perform):
  886.     /*  %rsi: old stack */
  887.         movq    Stack_handler(%rsi), %r11  /* %r11 := old stack -> handler */
  888.         movq    Handler_parent(%r11), %r10 /* %r10 := parent stack */
  889.         cmpq    $0, %r10                   /* parent is NULL? */
  890.         je      LBL(112)
  891.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS /* preserves r11 and rsi */
  892.      /* We have to null the Handler_parent after the switch because the
  893.         Handler_parent is needed to unwind the stack for backtraces */
  894.         movq    $0, Handler_parent(%r11) /* Set parent of performer to NULL */
  895.         movq    Handler_effect(%r11), %rsi  /* %rsi := effect handler */
  896.         jmp     GCALL(caml_apply3)
  897. LBL(112):
  898.     /* Switch back to original performer before raising Effect.Unhandled
  899.        (no-op unless this is a reperform) */
  900.         movq    0(%rbx), %r10  /* load performer stack from continuation */
  901.         subq    $1, %r10       /* r10 := Ptr_val(r10) */
  902.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %rsi
  903.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS
  904.     /* No parent stack. Raise Effect.Unhandled. */
  905.         movq    %rax, C_ARG_1
  906.         LEA_VAR(caml_raise_unhandled_effect, %rax)
  907.         jmp     LBL(caml_c_call)
  908. CFI_ENDPROC
  909. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_perform))

  911. FUNCTION(G(caml_reperform))
  912. CFI_STARTPROC
  913.     /*  %rax: effect to reperform
  914.         %rbx: continuation
  915.         %rdi: last_fiber */
  916.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %rsi  /* %rsi := old stack */
  917.         movq    (Stack_handler-1)(%rdi), %r10
  918.         movq    %rsi, Handler_parent(%r10)       /* Append to last_fiber */
  919.         leaq    1(%rsi), %rdi  /* %rdi (last_fiber) := Val_ptr(old stack) */
  920.      /* Need to update the oldest saved frame pointer here as the execution of
  921.         the handler may have caused the current fiber stack to reallocate. */
  922.         UPDATE_BASE_POINTER(%r10)
  923.         jmp     LBL(do_perform)
  924. CFI_ENDPROC
  925. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_reperform))

  927. FUNCTION(G(caml_resume))
  928. CFI_STARTPROC
  929.     /* %rax -> fiber, %rbx -> fun, %rdi -> arg */
  930.         leaq    -1(%rax), %r10  /* %r10 (new stack) = Ptr_val(%rax) */
  931.         movq    %rdi, %rax      /* %rax := argument to function in %rbx */
  932.     /*  check if stack null, then already used */
  933.         testq   %r10, %r10
  934.         jz      2f
  935.     /* Find end of list of stacks and add current */
  936.         movq    %r10, %rsi
  937. 1:      movq    Stack_handler(%rsi), %rcx
  938.         movq    Handler_parent(%rcx), %rsi
  939.         testq   %rsi, %rsi
  940.         jnz     1b
  941.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %rsi
  942.         movq    %rsi, Handler_parent(%rcx)
  943.      /* Need to update the oldest saved frame pointer here as the current fiber
  944.         stack may have been reallocated or we may be resuming a computation
  945.         that was not originally run here. */
  946.         UPDATE_BASE_POINTER(%rcx)
  947.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS
  948.         jmp     *(%rbx)
  949. 2:      LEA_VAR(caml_raise_continuation_already_resumed, %rax)
  950.         jmp LBL(caml_c_call)
  951. CFI_ENDPROC
  952. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_resume))

  954. /* Run a function on a new stack,
  955.    then invoke either the value or exception handler */
  956. FUNCTION(G(caml_runstack))
  957. CFI_STARTPROC
  958.         CFI_SIGNAL_FRAME
  959.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  960.     /* %rax -> fiber, %rbx -> fun, %rdi -> arg */
  961.         andq    $-2, %rax       /* %rax = Ptr_val(%rax) */
  962.     /* save old stack pointer and exception handler */
  963.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %rcx
  964.         movq    Caml_state(exn_handler), %r10
  965.         movq    %rsp, Stack_sp(%rcx)
  966.         movq    %r10, Stack_exception(%rcx)
  967.     /* Load new stack pointer and set parent */
  968.         movq    Stack_handler(%rax), %r11
  969.         movq    %rcx, Handler_parent(%r11)
  970.         movq    %rax, Caml_state(current_stack)
  971.         movq    Stack_sp(%rax), %r11
  972.     /* Create an exception handler on the target stack
  973.        after 16byte DWARF & gc_regs block (which is unused here) */
  974.         subq    $32, %r11
  975.         leaq    LBL(fiber_exn_handler)(%rip), %r10
  976.         movq    %r10, 8(%r11)
  977.     /* link the previous exn_handler so that copying stacks works */
  978.         movq    Stack_exception(%rax), %r10
  979.         movq    %r10, 0(%r11)
  980.         movq    %r11, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  981.     /* Switch to the new stack */
  982.         movq    %r11, %rsp
  983. #ifdef ASM_CFI_SUPPORTED
  984.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  985.         .cfi_escape DW_CFA_def_cfa_expression, 3+3+2, \
  986.           DW_OP_breg + DW_REG_rsp,                    \
  987.             16 /* exn */ +                            \
  988.             8 /* gc_regs slot (unused) */ +           \
  989.             8 /* C_STACK_SP for DWARF (unused) */     \
  990.             + Handler_parent, DW_OP_deref,            \
  991.           DW_OP_plus_uconst, Stack_sp, DW_OP_deref,   \
  992.           DW_OP_plus_uconst, RETADDR_ENTRY_SIZE
  993. #endif
  994.         movq    %rdi, %rax /* first argument */
  995.         callq   *(%rbx) /* closure in %rbx (second argument) */
  996. LBL(frame_runstack):
  997.         leaq    32(%rsp), %r11 /* SP with exn handler popped */
  998.         movq    Handler_value(%r11), %rbx
  999. 1:      movq    Caml_state(current_stack), C_ARG_1 /* arg to caml_free_stack */
  1000.     /* restore parent stack and exn_handler into Caml_state */
  1001.         movq    Handler_parent(%r11), %r10
  1002.         movq    Stack_exception(%r10), %r11
  1003.         movq    %r10, Caml_state(current_stack)
  1004.         movq    %r11, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  1005.     /* free old stack by switching directly to c_stack; is a no-alloc call */
  1006.         movq    Stack_sp(%r10), %r13 /* saved across C call */
  1007.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  1008.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  1009.         CFI_DEF_CFA_REGISTER(DW_REG_r13)
  1010.         movq    %rax, %r12 /* save %rax across C call */
  1011.         movq    Caml_state(c_stack), %rsp
  1012.         C_call  (GCALL(caml_free_stack))
  1013.     /* switch directly to parent stack with correct return */
  1014.         movq    %r13, %rsp
  1015.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  1016.         movq    %r12, %rax
  1017.     /* Invoke handle_value (or handle_exn) */
  1018.         LEAVE_FUNCTION
  1019.         jmp     *(%rbx)
  1020. LBL(fiber_exn_handler):
  1021.         leaq    16(%rsp), %r11
  1022.         movq    Handler_exception(%r11), %rbx
  1023.         jmp     1b
  1024. CFI_ENDPROC
  1025. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_runstack))

  1027. FUNCTION(G(caml_ml_array_bound_error))
  1028. CFI_STARTPROC
  1029.         ENTER_FUNCTION
  1030.         LEA_VAR(caml_array_bound_error_asm, %rax)
  1031.         jmp     LBL(caml_c_call)
  1032. CFI_ENDPROC
  1033. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_ml_array_bound_error))

  1035. FUNCTION(G(caml_assert_stack_invariants))
  1036. CFI_STARTPROC
  1037. /*      CHECK_STACK_ALIGNMENT */
  1038.         movq    Caml_state(current_stack), %r11
  1039.         movq    %rsp, %r10
  1040.         subq    %r11, %r10      /* %r10: number of bytes left on stack */
  1041.         /* can be two words over: the return addresses */
  1042.         cmp     $((Stack_threshold_words + Stack_ctx_words - 2)*8), %r10
  1043.         jge     1f
  1044.         int3
  1045. 1:      ret
  1046. CFI_ENDPROC
  1047. ENDFUNCTION(G(caml_assert_stack_invariants))

  1061.         .align  EIGHT_ALIGN

  1063.         .value  -1          /* negative frame size => use callback link */
  1064.         .value  0           /* no roots here */
